cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.SC 

This paper deals with the non-termination analysis of logic programs, which is a topic closely related to programming languages and software engineering. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves logical reasoning and inference, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with arithmetic operations, which could fall under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
